These two main political party faces with the low grades; however, Jamaica is an entire country. That includes judges.

The judges reflect the professionalism of the entire country. The judges are unqualified for their positions. Their behavior speak loudly of their low levels of professionalism.

That does not reflect that the entire country is unprofessional. It speaks for those one hundred sixty thousand people who make up the roles .

The Prime Minister said that in crime is on the rise in Jamaica. Well it should not come as a surprise to her when the judges have no problem in giving extremely light and lenient sentences that did not reflect the severity of the crime in nine out of ten cases.

Yes, violence is on the rise. Abuse, murders, rapes and robberies. No one is safe on the streets. There is also no justice doled out to the perpetrators.

Pure mayhem is now the order of the day in crime.

It is in all areas of Jamaica. The government will not take drastic measures to solve this crime issue. So, yes, crime is on the rise. For the sake of the innocent people of Jamaica, these judges need to be hanged.
